                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>„Bank Venezuela”</p>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Puerto Cabello</placeName>, <date>Septr 22<hi\n                        rend=\"sup\">nd</hi> 1854</date>.</p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Isaac Leeser Esq.</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">Dear sir,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Your esteemed lines <date>19<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> July</date> could\n                not be acknow-<lb/>ledged by the Dallett because I was rather unwell<lb/> at the\n                departure of said vessel.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I thank you extremely for the portrait and also<lb/> for the books,\n                the amount $9.38 will be handed<lb/> to you by <persName>Messrs. Dallett\n                    Brothers</persName> as per enclosed<lb/> order</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I regret exceedingly that I am not able to procure<lb/> the palms\n                and citrons for you; I have sent a man<lb/> to the country and he returned saying\n                that neither<lb/> of the two could be found. I trust that this fail-<lb/>ure will\n                not discourage you to command my ser-<lb/>-vice in future.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">If God please I will leave this about next week<lb/> to pass\n                    <date>Kipur</date> in <placeName>Curaçao</placeName> and will stay there<lb/>\n                four about six weeks, as my eldest son will complete<lb/> his thirteenth year, and\n                according to usage he is<lb/> preparing to read a portion of the law, which<lb/> law\n                I trust that himself and all my other chil-<lb/>dren will ever love and respect.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">If you can find a print of the Temple oblige<lb/> me to procure one\n                for me, and have it put in a<lb/> rose wood frame with gilt edges.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3hx16b1s/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
