                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3hx16b1s/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>I wish yourself and family long life and prospe<lb/>-rity and that you all may be\n                written in the book<lb/> of life &amp;c Is the sincere wish of</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">Dear sir,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">Yours, faithfully</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(4)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">A Myerston</persName>\n            </p>\n            <p>\n                <date>Septr 25th</date>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">We are but very few Israelites here, but we do<lb/> not feel the\n                less for our brethren in the <placeName>Holy Land</placeName>.<lb/> Our eldest\n                    <persName>Mr David Lobo</persName> is momently expected from<lb/> the Interior\n                and on his arrival we intend to meet<lb/> with the object of succouring our above\n                mentioned bro-<lb/>thers. Our contribution will be very scanty because we<lb/> are\n                most all men of family and depending entirely<lb/> in our gains as clerks and petty\n                merchants for a<lb/>\n                <sic>subsistance</sic>; were we in affluence we would be as<lb/> generous as our\n                other brothers abroad, but none of us<lb/> has the means of being liberal; however,\n                we are never<lb/> behind in contributing with our might to the cause<lb/> of\n                humanity</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(6)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">A M</persName>\n            </p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3hx16b1s/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
